According to the article, the United States has experienced a strong economic recovery under President Trump's leadership. The economy grew by 33.1% on an annualized basis in a single quarter, the largest in recorded history. The country has regained most of its pandemic-related loss of output and has exceeded experts' expectations. Consumption, housing, and private business investment have all seen significant increases. Automobile output has even increased by nearly 1,200%. The article credits President Trump's policies of low taxes, deregulation, improved trading conditions, and energy independence for the strong recovery. The article also highlights President Trump's response to the pandemic, including testing, PPE, treatments, and vaccine development, as well as support for small businesses, families, airlines, and local governments. Overall, the article suggests that the United States is on track to become the strongest and most inclusive economy ever.